A Parkgate wife made the horrific discovery of her husband’s hanged body at their Chelsea Gardens home, on Friday. The 53-year-old man was declared deceased on scene. Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA) members responded to the residence on Friday morning and found the victim lying on the bed. “Medics assessed the male patient and found that he showed no signs of life and died at the scene. “It was established that the deceased was found by his wife hanging from a burglar guard by a necktie. The necktie was cut by his son and the deceased was placed on the bed. The circumstances surrounding the deceased’s actions has not been established at this stage,” said RUSA head, Prem Balram.